    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Dear Molly,</></>A correction / clarification from Christine, who knows about such things: Thermal mass is more about material properties than mass, per se.  To wit: a big pile of wood does not hold heat better than a small slab of iron. And I would guess the ratio of volume to surface area may have something to do with it also.  But all this is not quite as pithy, now is it?  </></>Yours,</>Francis.</p>
    </div>

